            <thetext>When introducing namespaces for qooxdoo 0.5 the intention was to keep the class name itself (i.e. without the leading namespace prefix) unique across the entire framework. 

Example: there should only be one Button class (and a corresponding Button.js file) like qx.ui.form.Button, but no other say qx.foo.bar.Button anywhere else.

This leads to uglier names like qx.dom.DomElement instead of qx.dom.Element.

Shouldn&#39;t we drop the requirement (that doesn&#39;t work out currently anyway).</thetext>
